				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="dablink">For the critic of <a href="Hadith" title="Hadith">Hadith</a> and leader of <a href="Pakistan_Movement" title="Pakistan Movement">Pakistan Movement</a>, see <a href="Ghulam_Ahmed_Pervez" title="Ghulam Ahmed Pervez">Ghulam Ahmed Pervez</a>.</div>
<table class="infobox vcard" cellspacing="3" style="border-spacing: 3px; width:22em;">
<tr>
<th colspan="2" class="fn" style="text-align:center; font-size:125%; font-weight:bold; color:#FFFFFF; background-color: #708090">Mīrzā Ghulām Aḥmad</th>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Hazrat_Mirza_Ghulam_Ahmad.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/04/Hazrat_Mirza_Ghulam_Ahmad.jpg/220px-Hazrat_Mirza_Ghulam_Ahmad.jpg" width="220" height="293" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/04/Hazrat_Mirza_Ghulam_Ahmad.jpg/330px-Hazrat_Mirza_Ghulam_Ahmad.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/04/Hazrat_Mirza_Ghulam_Ahmad.jpg 2x" /></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center;">Founder of<br />
The Ahmadiyya Movement</th>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Full name</th>
<td class="nickname" style="">Mīrzā Ghulām Aḥmad</td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Titles</th>
<td class="" style="">Claimed to be <a href="Mujaddid" title="Mujaddid">Mujaddid</a> (divine reformer) of the fourteenth <a href="Islamic_calendar" title="Islamic calendar">Islamic century</a>, the Promised <a href="Messiah" title="Messiah">Messiah</a> (<a href="Second_Coming_of_Christ" title="Second Coming of Christ" class="mw-redirect">Second Coming of Christ</a>), and the <a href="Mahdi" title="Mahdi">Mahdi</a> awaited by the Muslims in the <a href="Islamic_eschatology" title="Islamic eschatology">end days</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-ReferenceA_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ReferenceA-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-ReferenceB_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ReferenceB-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Born</th>
<td class="" style=""><span style="display:none">(<span class="bday">1835-02-13</span>)</span>13 February 1835<br />
<a href="Qadian" title="Qadian">Qadian</a>, <a href="Sikh_Empire" title="Sikh Empire">Sikh Empire</a></td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Died</th>
<td class="" style="">26 May 1908<span style="display:none">(<span class="dday deathdate">1908-05-26</span>)</span> (aged&#160;73)<br />
<a href="Lahore" title="Lahore">Lahore</a>, <a href="British_Empire" title="British Empire">British Empire</a></td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Buried</th>
<td class="" style=""><a href="Bahishti_Maqbara" title="Bahishti Maqbara">Bahishti Maqbara</a>, <a href="Qadian" title="Qadian">Qadian</a>, India</td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Wives</th>
<td class="" style="">Hurmat Bibi<br />
Nusrat Jehan Begum</td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Offspring</th>
<td class="" style=""><a href="Mirza_Basheer-ud-Din_Mahmood_Ahmad" title="Mirza Basheer-ud-Din Mahmood Ahmad">Mirza Basheer-ud-Din Mahmood Ahmad</a><br />
Mirza Bashir Ahmad<br />
Mirza Sharif Ahmad<br />
Mubarika Begum<br />
Amatul Hafeez Begum</td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Father</th>
<td class="" style="">Mirza Ghulam Murtaza</td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Mother</th>
<td class="" style="">Chiragh Bibi</td>
</tr>
</table>
